	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99606861346687><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99606861346687>RE: A few questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99606861346687#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=67705><span id=Sage>Kensuke</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>85 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 9:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A bronze club is a bit heavy to be using. You'd be better off finding a splintering club. In the Freeport area, they usually come from orcs in the Oasis of Marr, and I'm sure there are some strewed about in the shops inside Freeport. If not, you may have to go to the Oasis of Marr, to the gypsy camp, and see if any of them are selling one. That's where people in Oasis go to do their selling. Getting a Sarnak Enforcer should be your first priority, though. <br><br>As to lightstones, anywhere willowisps live, you can get a lightstone from them. It's just that the better quality lightstone, the rarer it is. You might find somebody who's willing to sell you a greater lightstone for 5 plats, or even better, just give one to you. You could also buy a Split Paw Hide mask for 10pp's - 20pp's. That acts as a pretty powerful lightstone when worn, as well, and isn't too shabby of an item, as well. It's cheap, at least. =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
