	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Weight factor:<br>Monks have a limit to how much we can carry, after which we start taking SEVERE penalties to our Armor Class. You can find the exact numbers in the posts below. That's really all there is to it. 14lbs is max to begin but this increases slightly over time. You should ALWAYS be below your weight limit!<br><br>The difference in training with one or two 1hb weapons is quite small as long as you (ofcourse) hold a 1hb in your primary. This hands hits much more than the secondary, so I would say don't worry about it, or just use whatever you can get your hands on. Obviously, the lower delay of your practice weapons, the shorter it will take you to train. More strikes=More chances for skill-increases.<br><br>Any Wisp you kill drops a lightstone. Most are Burnt Out, but occasionally you get a "Lightstone" and on slightly rarer occasions you'll get a "Greater Lightstone". To my knowledge, there is no place where the better stones drop more frequently, so just go out there and slay the little buggers.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
