	   <a name=99605318641760></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99605318641760><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99605318641760>RE: What are monks good for.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99605318641760#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=57570><span id=Guru>Niteklaw</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>314 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 5:26 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'll take "The other aproach", and tell you about what's FUN and what's NOT about the monks. (Not fun could also be called "Limitations" instead. Semantics...)<br><br>FUN:<br>1) Looooots of damage dealt. No-one can open a can of Whoop-Ass like a monk.<br>2) Group if you like, solo if you like. You will never find yourself utterly dependant on others.<br>3) Versatility. Monks have many nice skills that make adventuring easier (Safe Fall, Sneak - which Rogues also have, so what's my point?)<br>4) Feign Death! What can I say? Other than being a nice tool for pulling, this skill outperforms any Gate, Evac, SoW, "Mesmerize-and-Flee-in-Terror" in the game as far as saving your life. Go ahead and Solo that Yellow Con if you like. You can always just abort (Ofcourse, later on the MoBs will start noticing that you weren't dead after all and come back for you).<br>5) Did I mention that Monks can kick butt like nobody's busines?<br>6) Getting Agro'ed on the occasional Corpse Run? Even a "Naked" monk can turn around and stop any oportinist MoB dead in his tracks.<br>7) I can't explain why, but monks are somehow rather "Cool".<br>8) Ouchie! Monks can really hurt people.<br><br>Not so much Fun:<br>1) Weight limits. If you are often going for D4 Ph4T L3wt, don't pick a monk. Loot one single heavy item and you'll have to run back to town before you can fight effectively again. You will also often see monks having to dump money everywhere too. Always painful.<br>2) You're a fighter, but so much nice fighter-equipment cannot be used by monks.<br>3) Monks are 100% offense, so don't think you can take all that much punishment. At higher levels you might often need another tank to taunt the MoBs away from you, and this can be difficult because of the massive damage you are dealing.<br>4) When in a group, YOU will always be picked as the primary puller. Expect to be running around looking for targets and splitting them while the others sit back, meditate, and talk about life's little mysteries.<br>5) Monks get some truly amazing equipment, but often have to make an amazing effort to obtain it.<br><br>But when all is said and done, the Monk is the most fun for me, and I've tried quite a few other things. (Necro, Chanter, Shadow Knight, Warrior, Cleric, Ranger, Rogue, well most classes, really).<br><br>Incidently, i DO envy the Rogues' ability to measure damage in KHP (Kilo-Hit Points), but hits like these are rare, and only under certain conditions. In a normal Man-to-Man fight, a monk generally deals more damage over time.<br><br>Niteklaw "Lean Green Fighting Machine" Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk with a high opinion of himself<br>Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
