	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My advice is to replace your old special attacks with the newer ones as you get it. <br><br>Once you get Flying Kick, that's all you'll be using, basically. You may want to keep Dragon Punch up in skill, since its faster refresh rate will sometimes allow you to interrupt a casting mobs spell, if you time it right. As for Kick, Round Kick, Eagle Strike and Tiger Claw, you'd probably be better off not using it. <br><br>Keep in mind, though, that if you're planning for this monk to be a long-term character, you'll get a discipline at level 59 called Silentfist, which uses Dragon Punch skill. At level 60 you'll get a discipline called Ashenhand, which uses Eagle Strike skill. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
