	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm not sure if killing the monks who hand out the sash's and headbands will get you the red sash/purple headband.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maybe Niteklaw can confirm that.  From what I've read, the only thing they drop is the black/blue versions, which are not used in the epic quest.<br><br>I'd start working on them while they still give you exp.  If you're in the mid 20s, the first 2 headbands are already green to you.  With the 2 monk heads from SK, you're nearly done with the red headband items.  You might not wear them, but when you get in the high 30s and start thinking about your first robe, you'll be glad they're in the bank.<br><br>I sold my purple headband to an iksar for what I thought was a huge sum of money, and it probably was.  But now I'm having to spend hours in SK looking for those heads...and very little there gives me exp.  It's not fun.<br>&nbsp;<br>Alerithon Tigerspirit<br>29 rank monk, E'Ci<br>Avatara</td></tr>
