	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although this is a somewhat brutal way of going about it, there is an alternate option:<br><br>By the time you're high eneough to start thinking about your Epic, you will probably know quite a few players in the high forties and fifties. I guarantee you that many of them have wrecked their Freeport and/or Qeynos factions, doing some of the more destructive quests. It would be rather easy (and FUN) to have some of your friends raid the monk guilds, and just hand you the headbands and sashes you need. This also has the added bonus of letting you get your hands on the Blue or Black sash/headband if you like. I am wearing the Blue Sash of Order because of just such a raid, and it's quite a nice item.<br><br>Anyway, the point of all this is, that if you get some people to go in with all guns blazing, so to speak, you can cut the time you spend getting these things down from hours on end to 2x10 minutes.<br><br>Just another option.<br><br>Niteklaw "I don't care, I worship Cazic Thule" Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar monk, Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
