	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 23rd 11:05 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>-Well, one interesting property about Greater Lightstones is that they can usually be bought from players for 7-8pp and then handed in for the Concordance of Research to somebody in South Ro (For evil races) and South Karana (for good races). The books you receive can the be sold to the person you got them from for 11-12pp. Sorry that this is a bit sketchy - I've only heard of this, never actually done it.<br><br>-The Iksar quests available to newbie monks are crap, IMHO, but if you look around town as a human, you can easily get 4-5-6 quests thrown at you too. As for the headbands and sashes, I will beat everyone to it and mention that an Iksar monk can easily get the ones he needs for his epic by handing the quest items (none of which are No Drop) to a dummy character who hands them in to the monk masters and then gives the headband or sash back to your Iksar.<br><br>-Mesh are nice for Wisp Hunting because they are magical, but they have no other properties. You can get an entire suit of Mesh Armor by (patiently) hunting Frogloks in the Innothule Swamp. If an item has an effect, it can generally be seen in the properties of the item (Right-Clicking).<br><br>-As for adding spice (and income): If you can actually hunt Wisps, do that. Perhaps try going to East or West Commonlands and hunting Giant Spiders. Good XP at lvl. 10 and they drop silk. Sell any swatches at 1pp a piece. For something a bit more exciting, see if you can get anyone to help you to The Field of Bone in Kunark (You can be bound in Kaesora). This is one of the best low-level zones in the game, with lots of good xp and all the animals there carry cash (!) You will have to get help trading and banking, though, and come to think of it, this suggestion might suck...But you wanted spice, and there you have it.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
