	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 3:03 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.24]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not sure what your money situation is.<br><br>But, at your level, Cured Silk or Wu's should do just fine. You should invest in a good 1HB (Sarnak Enforcer's a good choice for around 50 pp's, or if you can afford it, a Fighting Baton.) <br><br>Also remember to keep up both your 1HB skill and Hand to Hand skill maxxed each level. And try to pick up a bamboo bo stick for around 100 pp's to start getting your 2HB skill up. <br><br>Armor can go any number of ways, but it mostly relies on your money situation. If you're skimping for money right now, you should do just fine for a while with the Wu's stuff. When you start getting more money (for a Freeport monk, this probably won't happen until the 20's) you should start switching out the Wu's for better pieces. <br><br>For chest, try for a foreman's tunic. <br>Vox bracers are good for wrists. <br>Executioner's hood is good for head. <br>Gem-inlaid gauntlets are good for hands. <br>A thick leather apron is good for a belt. <br>For rings, try for some +AC and +HP rings. Fire wedding rings, with better metals giving more bonuses. <br>Orc fang earrings are good for ears. <br>Masks can go any number of ways. <br>For neck, an orc fang necklace or Ulthork hide collar should suffice. <br><br>As to where to buy this stuff, check out East Commons. It's generally accepted that that's the "auction" zone. People go there to buy and sell. Just send out an auction that you WTB (want to buy) certain items, and if someone has one for sale, they'll notify you. If no one notifies you, it might be that someone just doesn't have one for sale, or if they do, they missed your message. Just keep a careful eye out, and don't spam. As a warning, though, certain items, especially the Sarnak Enforcer and bamboo bo stick, do not go up for sale quite often, so it may be a while before you find someone selling them.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
